READ ME: The Student class extends Person, adding a school name and student ID.
It includes methods to retrieve school details and overrides toString() to display the studentâ€™s name and institution.

// Connor Edwards, Assignment 3

public class Student extends Person {
    protected int sId;
    protected String school;

    // Constructor to initialize Student with ID, name, school, and student ID
    public Student(int id, String name, String school, int sId) {
        super(id, name);
        this.school = school;
        this.sId = sId;
    }

    // Getter for school
    public String getSchool() {
        return school;
    }

    // Getter for student ID
    public int getSId() {
        return sId;
    }

    // Override toString method to provide a formatted string representation
    @Override
    public String toString() {
        return "Student: " + name + " at " + school;
    }
}
